<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880120-0049 </DOCNO><HL> National Education Unit Plans to Redeem Debentures Due 2011 </HL><SO> </SO><CO> NEC </CO><IN> BBK </IN><DATELINE> IRVINE, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   National Education Corp. said its Advanced Systems Inc. unit will redeem Feb. 24 its $30 million outstanding of 7% convertible subordinated debentures due 2011.    The redemption price is $1,096.83 for each $1,000 principal amount of debentures, including $33.83 accrued interest. The debentures are currently convertible into shares of National Education common at $11.722 a share, or about 85.31 shares of National Education common for each $1,000 of debentures. National Education has about 25 million common shares outstanding.    National Education closed yesterday at $19.125, down 37.5 cents, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading. Based on that price, debenture holders would receive stock with a market value of $1,631.55 for each $1,000 principal amount of debentures if they convert their debt.    As previously reported, National Education, a vocational training company, acquired Arlington Heights, Ill.,-based Advanced Systems last month. </TEXT></DOC>